rComments: Didnt learn anything

The textbook is your best tool in his class. He cares a lot about the feedback from his students and is available to answer questions outside of class hours. He is not a hard grader, but the communication between him and his TAs could have been stronger. They were not all grading according to the same criteria which left many students confused.

Martin Kalumbabi was by far the best teacher I had all throughout my first year. I am in first year and could not imagine taking a second year course as an elective due to the fact I was scared and nervous but I was beyond excited to later on find out how amazing, hilarious and welcoming the prof truly was. I would definitely retake the course!

Je lui ai posé une question après un cours à propos du cours et il m'a envoyé promené. La matière aurait pu être franchement intéressante, mais il pouvait être ennuyant. Il parlait qu'avec les mêmes 4-5 personnes durant le cours. Il pouvait créer des débats intéressants, mais il manque de précision dans ses travaux. Il a l'air d'être assez sévère

J'ai pour ma part adoré ce professeur, je me sens marginal dans mes allégations, mais il est un excellent pédagoge! Il connaît bien la matière et il enseigne d'une manière qui nécessite la lecture des textes et l'écoute pendant les cours! Oublier votre cellulaire et votre Facebook, la bête noire de plusieurs! Les attentes sont raisonnables!!

This course was double-edged, as the subject seemed very interesting at first. Overall, it was up and down, as a result of the delivery by the professor, who was often scattered and unclear in his explanations. The subject was interesting, nonetheless, and self-teaching was doable. Easy enough class, but could've been much better.
The best teacher I ever had!!

He is awful! He moves quickly between points.  He is hard to understand, swears often, laughs at students' questions, and does not use blackboard at all. He is one of the worst proffs I've ever had! Do NOT take this class!

Wow! He doesn't use blackboard at all so attending class in mandatory at all coasts. He is very confusing in his lectures- jumps from point A to D then back to B.. His ultimate goal is to make the most people fail as he expressed in one of his lectures. Not a very nice person overall, I would not recommend him as a teacher.

Really unhelpful and sometimes came off as rude when 'answering' students' questions. He seemed confused by his own ideas and material, and was difficult to follow. He won't use any powerpoint or anything that needs the use of a computer really. The TA was just as bad. I decided to drop the class, and take it with another prof.

The teaching was not very stimulating (although having class at 8:30 and 10 am does not help). There were readings but they are not on the exam. The material (if you like religion) was so interesting! First midterm was hard, final was kind of easy if you studied well (you have about 11 religions to memorize). I loved the class, just not the prof.
VERY GOOD TEACHER, YOU NEED TO ATTEND CLASSES IN ORDER TO UNDERSTAND THE COURSE...HE TAKES TIME TO ANSWER YOUR QUESTIONS IF YOU GO SEE HIM AT HIS OFFICE!EXCELLENT TEACHER!

Terrible experience with this prof. Will not make any effort to help students, even if the student makes repeated efforts. His goal is not to help students reach their goals, it is simply to get through the material and get done with it. The definition of a terrible prof. Do not take his course!

N'a aucune gérance de classe, fini souvent le cours sans finir la matière. N'est pas claire dans son enseignement  et manque beaucoup de détails qui son obligatoire pour les examens. Les assistantes son très sévères. Ne pas prendre ce cours.

You have to attend class to understand the material. Hardly ever responds to e-mails and you have to pay very close attention to what he is saying to make sure that you understand. He is very knowledgable in his subject but overall is a bad prof.

Very hard to understand in class, doesn't use virtual campus/powerpoints/overheads/anything, takes a week or more to respond to emails, not flexible with meeting if you are unable to make it to his office hours. The course material is pretty interesting, but he is just not a good prof.
Not a good teacher !

Il est super interessant comme prof, et sait bien comment presenter ses idees dans une belle maniere. Les examens exigent la comprehension et la capacité de synthetiser la matière du cours - pas de memorisation.

avec se prof c'est pas complique plus que ta l'aire intéresse, tu prend de belle note plus que ta note sera élevé. les examens sont exactement se qu'il dit en classe et les textes sont complémentaire.avec c'est deux chose vous parte avec un A- garantie...vraiment facile et drôle comme prof
Very hard to understand at the best of times. Not a bad professor, but you need to listen very closely and ask to repeat often
